What is the purpose of the [::.emacs.d] directory?

The directory ##~/.emacs.d/## is a standard location for your own configuration files, your own developments, or external third-party modes.  For example, starting with EmacsÂ 22, if the [[init file]] ##~/.emacs## does not exist, Emacs will try ##~/.emacs.d/init.el## or ##~/.emacs.d/init.elc##.  You can also put the shell init file ##.emacs_SHELL## under ##~/.emacs.d##.
The directory ##~/.emacs.d/## is not shipped by the operating system distributor--e.g. Debian, Suse, etc--which means it will not be overwritten by a re-installation. 

